episodes.title: The Butter Shave
episodes.plot: Kramer discovers the amazing yet unknown uses of butter, but accidentally fries himself after using it as sunscreen.

episodes.title: The Voice
episodes.plot: George's colleagues try to force him to leave. Jerry makes fun of his girlfriend's bellybutton. Kramer hires an intern. Elaine gets back together with David Puddy.

episodes.title: The Serenity Now
episodes.plot: Jerry opens up his feelings. Elaine is getting hit on by the Jews. Kramer gets a screen door. George helps his father sell computers.

episodes.title: The Blood
episodes.plot: Jerry's parents hire their friend Izzy Mandelbaum to become Jerry's personal trainer while George decides to associate food and television with his love life.

episodes.title: The Junk Mail
episodes.plot: Kramer is annoyed with the catalogs he keeps getting in the mail. Elaine falls in love with a guy because of his smile. George's parents are avoiding him. Jerry can't find it in his heart to reject a gift from an old school friend.

episodes.title: The Merv Griffin Show
episodes.plot: George runs over a flock of pigeons. Jerry's girlfriend has a vintage toy collection she won't let him touch. A new co-worker is freaking Elaine out. Kramer rebuilds the set of "The Merv Griffin Show" in his apartment.

episodes.title: The Slicer
episodes.plot: Elaine borrows Kramer's meat slicer to feed her neighbor's cat while George tries to hide his not-so-great past from his new boss.

episodes.title: The Betrayal
episodes.plot: Elaine and the gang head to India to attend a wedding; Jerry betrays George by having sex with his prospective girlfriend; Kramer grapples with a malignant wish.

episodes.title: The Apology
episodes.plot: George is angered when an old acquaintance withholds a 12-Step-mandated apology; Jerry's girlfriend is too comfortable with her nudity; Elaine works with a germaphobe.

episodes.title: The Strike
episodes.plot: Jerry goes out with a woman who is beautiful one day and ugly the next. Kramer goes back to work at H&H Bagels. George makes up a charity. Elaine gives a fake number to a man.

episodes.title: The Dealership
episodes.plot: Jerry looks to buy a new car from Elaine's boyfriend. George tries to find a snack. Kramer test drives a car.

episodes.title: The Reverse Peephole
episodes.plot: Elaine is embarrassed by Puddy's fur coat. Kramer tries to keep Newman from getting evicted. George carries everything in his wallet. Jerry is through with wallets.

episodes.title: The Cartoon
episodes.plot: Sally Weaver makes fun of Jerry. George's new girlfriend looks just like Jerry. Kramer takes a vow of silence. Elaine gets a job drawing cartoons for the New Yorker.

episodes.title: The Strongbox
episodes.plot: George's new girlfriend refuses to break up with him. Jerry doesn't help out a neighbor. Elaine's new boyfriend is poor. Kramer tries to find a good place to hide his key for his strongbox.

episodes.title: The Wizard
episodes.plot: Jerry goes down to Florida for his father's birthday. George tries to avoid Susan's parents. Elaine can't figure out her new boyfriend's nationality. Kramer decides to retire.

episodes.title: The Burning
episodes.plot: Elaine finds out that Puddy is religious. Kramer pretends to have gonorrhea. Jerry's new girlfriend has a tractor story to tell him. George wants everyone at work to like him.

episodes.title: The Bookstore
episodes.plot: George is forced to buy a book he took with him into the bathroom. Jerry finds out that his Uncle Leo is a shoplifter. Elaine doesn't want to be known as the office skank. Kramer and Newman start a Hong Kong rickshaw business.

episodes.title: The Frogger
episodes.plot: George is obsessed with preserving his Frogger high score for posterity; Jerry stays one step ahead of a serial killer; Elaine eats Peterman's expensive cake:

episodes.title: The Maid
episodes.plot: Jerry gets into romance with his maid; George struggles to get the nickname "T-Bone" around the office; Elaine searches for a new telephone number.

episodes.title: The Puerto Rican Day
episodes.plot: Jerry, George, Kramer and Elaine get stuck in standstill traffic due to the massive Puerto Rican Day Parade.

episodes.title: The Chronicle
episodes.plot: Just as the four are about to go to the movies, Jerry looks back on the past nine years with the audience.

episodes.title: The Finale
episodes.plot: After George and Jerry land a production deal with NBC, the four head out for Paris on NBC's private plane and are waylaid in a small Massachusetts town.
